niagara.optimizer.colombia
Class Cost

java.lang.Object
  niagara.optimizer.colombia.Cost

public class Cost
extends java.lang.Object

Cost of executing a physical operator, expression or multiexpression Cost cannot be associated with a multiexpression, since cost is determined by properties desired. For example, a SELECT will cost more if sorted is required. Cost value of -1 = infinite cost. Any other negative cost is considered an error.
